<h1>Problem 712 - 2020 CMC, P8 of 8</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 9</h2>
<p>Let \(a_{1}, a_{2}, \ldots\) be an infinite sequence of positive real numbers such that for each positive integer \(n\) we have \[\frac{a_{1}+a_{2}+\cdots+a_{n}}{n} \geq \sqrt{\frac{a_{1}^{2}+a_{2}^{2}+\cdots+a_{n+1}^{2}}{n+1}}\] Prove that the sequence \(a_{1}, a_{2}, \ldots\) is constant.</p>
